<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-6878] camel-cxf-transport component does not include Content-Type in the map of headers</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-6878</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;See &lt;a href=&quot;http://camel.465427.n5.nabble.com/CFX-Bean-headers-access-Issue-tt5741312.html#a5741691&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://camel.465427.n5.nabble.com/CFX-Bean-headers-access-Issue-tt5741312.html#a5741691&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Content-Type is HTTP header like all other headers are, CXF typically has it in the headers map and also as a dedicated message property.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;At the moment Camel CXF sets Content-Type only as a message property and not adds it to the list of the headers. This is not consistent with the default CXF HTTP processing.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
